<td width="20%" height="17" align="center" valign="top"> Running Costs</td>
<td width="26%" height="17" align="center" valign="top"> Total Expenditure</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="14%" height="17" align="left" valign="bottom"> 2001-02</td>
<td width="41%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;109,000</td>
<td width="20%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;29,200</td>
<td width="26%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;138,200</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="14%" height="17" align="left" valign="bottom"> 2002-03</td>
<td width="41%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;140,800</td>
<td width="20%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;28,400</td>
<td width="26%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;169,200</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="14%" height="17" align="left" valign="bottom"> 2003-04</td>
<td width="41%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;82,000</td>
<td width="20%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;31,400</td>
<td width="26%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;113,400</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="14%" height="17" align="left" valign="bottom"> 2004-05</td>
<td width="41%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;51,400</td>
<td width="20%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;30,600</td>
<td width="26%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;82,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="14%" height="17" align="left" valign="bottom"> 2005-06</td>
<td width="41%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;75,500</td>
<td width="20%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;35,500</td>
<td width="26%" height="17" align="right" valign="middle">&pound;111,000</td>
</tr>
</table></p>

  <p>In addition, we expect this year to pay backdated rent in respect of 2005-06 once the new agreement for the use of Bute House has been concluded. Business rates are included in running costs and the Assessor, Lothian Valuation Joint Board has recently confirmed that there is no element of residential accommodation within Bute House that will attract a council tax charge.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-12-22.6.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa1222.htm#5">Scottish Executive Expenditure</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-12-22.6.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80095" speakername="Alex Neil (Central Scotland) (SNP)" spid="S2W-30427" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa1222.htm#5" holdingdate="2006-12-21">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether it has any plans to improve Government Expenditure and Revenue in Scotland in line with the UK Government&rsquo;s plans to create an independent board to enhance confidence in government statistics, as announced in the Queen&rsquo;s Speech.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-12-22.6.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80077" speakername="Mr Tom McCabe" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa1222.htm#5">

  <p>I refer the member to the question S2W-30426 answered on 21 December 2006. All answers to written parliamentary questions are available on the Parliament&rsquo;s website, the search facility for which can be found at: <a href="../../../webapp/wa.search">http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/webapp/wa.search</a> .</p>

  <p>Government Expenditure and Revenue in Scotland is based on the latest available, official fiscal data. The estimates for government expenditure and revenues are produced using methodological best practice which is subject to on-going review.</p>

</reply>
